'generate_query[1].predict' predictor demos: [Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Smith &amp; Carrier | Smith & Carrier was an architectural partnership based in Asheville, North Carolina. It was formed in 1906 as a partnership of Richard Sharp Smith (1852–1924) and Albert Heath Carrier (1878–1961).', "Smith's Food and Drug | Smith's Food & Drug Centers, Inc. was founded in 1911 in Brigham City, Utah, United States by Lorenzo J. Smith. Now a subsidiary of The Kroger Company, it is a prominent regional supermarket chain operating in the Southwest, Northwest, and Tennessee. After completing a merger with Portland-based Fred Meyer in 1997, Fred Meyer was in turn acquired by Cincinnati-based Kroger in 1999, making Kroger the largest supermarket chain in the United States. Smith's headquarters are in Salt Lake City.", 'The Smiths | The Smiths were an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1982. The band consisted of vocalist Morrissey, guitarist Johnny Marr, bassist Andy Rourke and drummer Mike Joyce. Critics have called them the most important alternative rock band to emerge from the British independent music scene of the 1980s." Q" magazine\'s Simon Goddard argued in 2007 that the Smiths were "the one truly vital voice of the \'80s", "the most influential British guitar group of the decade" and the "first indie outsiders to achieve mainstream success on their own terms". The "NME" named the Smiths the "most influential artist ever" in a 2002 poll, over the Beatles.'], 'question': 'Were The Smiths and Filter formed in the same city?', 'reasoning': "The context provides information about The Smiths, an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1982. However, there is no information about Filter's formation location in the given context. Therefore, we cannot determine from the given information if The Smiths and Filter were formed in the same city.", 'search_query': 'Where was Filter, the American rock band, formed?'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Alton Davis | Alton Thomas Davis (born c. 1946-47) is a former member of the Supreme Court of Michigan, United States. Davis was appointed by former Governor Jennifer Granholm on August 26, 2010 to finish the term of former Justice Elizabeth Weaver, who resigned from the court amidst controversy.', "1904 Democratic National Convention | The 1904 Democratic National Convention was a United States presidential nominating convention that took place during the 1904 World's Fair and the 1904 Summer Olympics in the Coliseum of the St. Louis Exposition and Music Hall in St. Louis, Missouri. The convention nominated Alton B. Parker of New York for President and Henry G. Davis of West Virginia for Vice President. The ticket lost the 1904 presidential election to the Republican Party ticket of Theodore Roosevelt and Charles W. Fairbanks.", 'Harry L. Davis | Harry Lyman Davis (January 25, 1878 – May 21, 1950) was an American politician of the Republican Party. He served as the 38th and 44th mayor of Cleveland, Ohio and as the 49th Governor of Ohio.'], 'question': 'What party does the governor that appointed Alton Davis belong to?', 'reasoning': 'From the context, we know that Alton Davis was appointed to the Supreme Court of Michigan by Governor Jennifer Granholm. The question asks for the political party of the governor who appointed Alton Davis. We need to find out which political party Jennifer Granholm belongs to.', 'search_query': 'What is the political party of Jennifer Granholm?'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Lamar Holmes | Lamar Holmes (born July 8, 1989) is a Canadian football offensive tackle for the Hamilton Tiger-Cats of the Canadian Football League (CFL). He was drafted by the Atlanta Falcons in the third round of the 2012 NFL Draft. Holmes played college football at Southern Miss. He is from Gastonia, North Carolina and attended Hunter Huss High School.', 'Lester Holmes | Lester Holmes (born September 27, 1969 in Tylertown, Mississippi) is a former American football offensive lineman in the National Football League. He played college football at Jackson State University and was drafted in the first round of the 1993 NFL Draft.', 'Jaret Holmes | Jaret D. Holmes (born March 3, 1976) is a former American football placekicker in the National Football League for the Chicago Bears (1999), the New York Giants (2000) and the Jacksonville Jaguars (2001). He played high school football at Clinton High School. Holmes played college football at Hinds Community College and Auburn University.'], 'question': 'Lamar Holmes played college football at a university located in what city?', 'reasoning': 'The context mentions that Lamar Holmes played college football at Southern Miss. To find the city where Southern Miss is located, we need to formulate a search query.', 'search_query': 'What city is Southern Miss located in?'}) (input_keys=None)]

'generate_answer.predict' predictor demos: [Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Smith &amp; Carrier | Smith & Carrier was an architectural partnership based in Asheville, North Carolina. It was formed in 1906 as a partnership of Richard Sharp Smith (1852–1924) and Albert Heath Carrier (1878–1961).', "Smith's Food and Drug | Smith's Food & Drug Centers, Inc. was founded in 1911 in Brigham City, Utah, United States by Lorenzo J. Smith. Now a subsidiary of The Kroger Company, it is a prominent regional supermarket chain operating in the Southwest, Northwest, and Tennessee. After completing a merger with Portland-based Fred Meyer in 1997, Fred Meyer was in turn acquired by Cincinnati-based Kroger in 1999, making Kroger the largest supermarket chain in the United States. Smith's headquarters are in Salt Lake City.", 'The Smiths | The Smiths were an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1982. The band consisted of vocalist Morrissey, guitarist Johnny Marr, bassist Andy Rourke and drummer Mike Joyce. Critics have called them the most important alternative rock band to emerge from the British independent music scene of the 1980s." Q" magazine\'s Simon Goddard argued in 2007 that the Smiths were "the one truly vital voice of the \'80s", "the most influential British guitar group of the decade" and the "first indie outsiders to achieve mainstream success on their own terms". The "NME" named the Smiths the "most influential artist ever" in a 2002 poll, over the Beatles.', 'Filter (band) | Filter is an American industrial rock group formed in 1993 in Cleveland by singer Richard Patrick and guitarist/programmer Brian Liesegang. The band was formed after Patrick desired to start his own band after leaving Nine Inch Nails as their touring guitarist. Their debut album, "Short Bus", was released in 1995, and ended up going platinum, selling over one million copies, largely due to the success of the band\'s single "Hey Man Nice Shot." After the album, the band would go through the first of many line-up changes, leaving Patrick as the only consistent member across all music releases.', 'The Golden Filter | The Golden Filter is an American/Australian electronic music duo from New York City, formed in 2008, now based in London. The band consists of Penelope Trappes and Stephen Hindman.', 'Afektiven Naboj | Afektiven Naboj (Macedonian: Афективен Набој ) was one of the two punk rock bands (the other being "Filter") formed in 1979 by guitar player Klime Kovaceski and Goran Trajkoski, now an eminent musician from Republic of Macedonia, who rose to international prominence as a frontman of the group Anastasia featured on the soundtrack album for the Academy Award nominated Milčo Mančevski\'s film "Before the Rain".'], 'question': 'Were The Smiths and Filter formed in the same city?', 'reasoning': 'The context provides information about The Smiths, which were formed in Manchester, England, and Filter, which was formed in Cleveland, Ohio, USA. Since Manchester and Cleveland are different cities, The Smiths and Filter were not formed in the same city.', 'answer': 'No'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Alton Davis | Alton Thomas Davis (born c. 1946-47) is a former member of the Supreme Court of Michigan, United States. Davis was appointed by former Governor Jennifer Granholm on August 26, 2010 to finish the term of former Justice Elizabeth Weaver, who resigned from the court amidst controversy.', "1904 Democratic National Convention | The 1904 Democratic National Convention was a United States presidential nominating convention that took place during the 1904 World's Fair and the 1904 Summer Olympics in the Coliseum of the St. Louis Exposition and Music Hall in St. Louis, Missouri. The convention nominated Alton B. Parker of New York for President and Henry G. Davis of West Virginia for Vice President. The ticket lost the 1904 presidential election to the Republican Party ticket of Theodore Roosevelt and Charles W. Fairbanks.", 'Harry L. Davis | Harry Lyman Davis (January 25, 1878 – May 21, 1950) was an American politician of the Republican Party. He served as the 38th and 44th mayor of Cleveland, Ohio and as the 49th Governor of Ohio.', 'Jennifer Granholm | Jennifer Mulhern Granholm (born February 5, 1959) is a Canadian-American politician, lawyer, educator, author, political commentator and member of the Democratic Party who served as the Attorney General of Michigan from 1999 to 2003 and as the Governor of Michigan from 2003 to 2011. She is currently an MSNBC political contributor. In January 2017, she became a CNN political contributor.', 'Michigan gubernatorial election, 2006 | The Michigan gubernatorial election of 2006 was one of the 36 U.S. gubernatorial elections held November 7, 2006. Incumbent Democratic Governor Jennifer Granholm was re-elected over Republican businessman Dick DeVos and three minor party candidates. Granholm was re-elected with 56% of the vote.', 'Michigan gubernatorial election, 2010 | The Michigan gubernatorial election of 2010 was held on November 2, 2010. Incumbent Democratic Governor Jennifer Granholm was prohibited by the state\'s Constitution from seeking a third term. This resulted in a large pool of candidates which was whittled down, when the May 11 filing deadline passed, to two Democrats and five Republicans. Both the "Cook Political Report" and the non-partisan "Rothenberg Political Report" rated the election as leaning Republican.'], 'question': 'What party does the governor that appointed Alton Davis belong to?', 'reasoning': 'From the context, we know that Jennifer Granholm, who is a member of the Democratic Party, appointed Alton Davis to the Supreme Court of Michigan. Therefore, the party of the governor that appointed Alton Davis is the Democratic Party.', 'answer': 'Democratic Party'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Lamar Holmes | Lamar Holmes (born July 8, 1989) is a Canadian football offensive tackle for the Hamilton Tiger-Cats of the Canadian Football League (CFL). He was drafted by the Atlanta Falcons in the third round of the 2012 NFL Draft. Holmes played college football at Southern Miss. He is from Gastonia, North Carolina and attended Hunter Huss High School.', 'Lester Holmes | Lester Holmes (born September 27, 1969 in Tylertown, Mississippi) is a former American football offensive lineman in the National Football League. He played college football at Jackson State University and was drafted in the first round of the 1993 NFL Draft.', 'Jaret Holmes | Jaret D. Holmes (born March 3, 1976) is a former American football placekicker in the National Football League for the Chicago Bears (1999), the New York Giants (2000) and the Jacksonville Jaguars (2001). He played high school football at Clinton High School. Holmes played college football at Hinds Community College and Auburn University.', 'University of Southern Mississippi | The University of Southern Mississippi, known informally as Southern Miss, is a public research university located in Hattiesburg, Mississippi. It is situated 70 mi north of Gulfport, Mississippi and 105 mi northeast of New Orleans, Louisiana. Southern Miss is accredited by the Commission on Colleges of the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools (SACS) to award baccalaureate, master\'s, specialist, and doctoral degrees. The university is classified by the Carnegie Foundation as a "Research University" with "High Research Activity" (designation "RU/H").', 'Pete Taylor Park | Pete Taylor Park is a baseball stadium located in Hattiesburg, Mississippi, that is home to the Southern Miss Golden Eagles baseball team.', 'Battle for the Bell (Southern Miss vs Tulane) | The Battle for the Bell is an American college football rivalry game between the University of Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles and Tulane University Green Wave football teams. The two schools are located about 110 miles from each other (Southern Miss in Hattiesburg, Mississippi, and Tulane in New Orleans, Louisiana) via Interstate 10 and Interstate 59, making for a heated game.'], 'question': 'Lamar Holmes played college football at a university located in what city?', 'reasoning': 'The context mentions that Lamar Holmes was drafted by the Atlanta Falcons in the 2012 NFL Draft and played college football at Southern Miss. The context also provides information about the University of Southern Mississippi, indicating that it is located in Hattiesburg, Mississippi.', 'answer': 'Hattiesburg'}) (input_keys=None)]

